               <msContents>
                  <summary>Maṣḥafa qǝddāse “Missal” (fols. 8ra-109va)
 I) Daily Office Prayers
                     and Litanies (fols. 8ra-24rb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass”
                     (fols. 24rb-48vb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols. 48vb-109va)
 III-1) Anaphora
                     of the Apostles (fols. 48vb-58ra)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ
                     (fols. 58va-60va)
 - Excerpt from “Testament of Our Lord” (fol.
                     58ra-va)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols.
                     60vb-66vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John, Son of Thunder (fols.
                     66vb-72rb)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 72rb-75va)
                     III-6) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 75va-76vb)
 III-7)
                     Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 76vb-81va)
 III-8)
                     Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 81va-86vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St
                     Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 87ra-90rb)
 III-10)
                     Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 90rb-96vb)
 III-11) Anaphora
                     of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 96vb-100va)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Jacob
                     of Serug (fols. 100va-104ra)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria
                     (fols. 104ra-107va)
 III-14) Second Anaphora of St Gregory
                     (“Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 107vb-109va)
 
 Additiones
                     1-2; Colophon.</summary>
