                           <item>ቡ፡ for ቡራኬ፡</item>
                           <item>እ፡ for እማሬ፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ተ፡ እ፡</abbr> for <expan>ተዘከር፡ እግዚኦ፡ </expan> (s. <locus target="#44ra">44ra-</locus>rb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ስብ፡ ወእ፡ ይእ፡ ወዘ፡ ወለዓ፡ ዓለ፡</abbr> for <expan>ስብሐት፡ ወእኂዝ፡ ይእዜኒ፡
                                 ወዘልፈኒ፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (s. <locus target="#20ra">20ra</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the ruling King; names in
                           supplication formulas (pink); incipits and headings of the texts; incipit
                           of fol. 9r and the incipits of most Anaphoras are written alternately in
                           red and black linesdirectives for the ministers; some of the musical
                           notation signs above the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#6r">f. 6r: </locus>
                        <desc>Schematic representation of the Eucharistic bread and its distribution
                           among the participants of the Liturgy.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"/>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#6ra">ff. 6ra-7</locus>
                           <desc>ra: Explanations or commentary (ʾandǝmta?) concerning the fraction
                              of the Eucharistic bread.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in Amharic. The text is divided into five sections
                              treating different subjects: Prayer of Fraction; exactness of
                              measurements (of the bread and wine for the Eucharist?); Holy
                              Communion received by priests; priestly blessings (last two sections).
                              The text is written around the a schematic representation of the
                              Eucharistic bread. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#7ra">f. 7ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb: Regulations concerning liturgical occasions on which
                              particular Anaphoras are to be celebrated.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The regulations are in Amharic, but most of the text consists of
                              names of liturgical occasions and Anaphoras in Gǝʿǝz. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes in upper margin: <locus target="#26v">26v</locus>, 54r, 67r, 72r, 76v, 77r, 81v, 87r, 90r, 96v, 99r, 100r,
                           100v, 103r, 104r, 107v.
 -Tamallas signs in the shape of ┴ indicating
                           the place where the omissions, written in the upper margins, belong, in
                           fols: 17v l.1, 60ra l.14, 64ra l.8, 65rb l.21, 66va l.1, 68rb l.7, 77ra
                           l.4.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
